      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOOSE MOOSE (2) continues to race well but is struggling to break through, placing at his last four runs. Last time finished 3rd on June 25 over 595m at Angle Park behind Adhana Martina beaten 2.5 lengths (35.26) in a Grade 6. One of the contenders. JUST A NUISANCE (4) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a 1.75 lengths win at Angle Park in a handy 34.73. Awkwardly drawn but goes well over this trip. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Leading chance again. WHITE HAWKE (1) missed the frame last time when sixth (31.18) at Angle Park but prior to that had two placings in a row. Goes very well here finding the frame in each of four starts. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and six minor placings to his credit. Deserves plenty of respect. BRINK AND BACK (3) returns from a six-and-a-half weeks layoff and must be considered.",
